TRICKY MAGICIAN tracked on the rail well in hand watching the top pair with three furlongs to run, was in range of the leader inside straightening out for the drive, shifted just off the fence to bid between rivals three sixteenths from the wire, battled stubbornly between in deep stretch but was just outgamed by the winner in the end. CRAFTY CONQUEST had an uncontested lead down the backside and through the turn, continued to be alone at the top of the lane, began to get leg weary at the furlong pole, was collared in deep stretch but still held for a clear third. HIGHLAND SOCIETY chased the frontrunner down the backside, continued to follow the pacesetter on the turn and yielded between runners in mid stretch. SEA SCOUT stalked near the rear in the beginning stages, was roused five wide behind horses at the top of the lane but could not get involved down the stretch. MIDNIGHT MEADOW was off a bit slow to begin, trailed the field down the backstretch, angled six deep at the top of the lane , was steadied to avoid fallen rival, was not persevered with afterwards and walked across the finish line. AL HEYBAY settled near the rear in the early going, commenced a run six wide turning for home, was steadied sharply trying avoid the fallen foe and galloped across the finish line. UNCLE BULL had a good tracking spot outside watching the top two throughout the turn, rallied four wide with runners on either side at the quarter pole, was in tight surroundings in upper stretch driving to the finish, clipped heels, fell and walked off. STEWARDS INQUIRY REGARDING THE STRETCH RUN RESULTED IN NO CHANGE

SILENT GHOST had a narrow lead being pressed outside at the half, was collared by the winner inside midway on the turn, determinedly dug in four deep through the stretch to settled for a clear third in the end. LOIS LEN pressed the pace outside down the backstretch, could not match strides with the leaders with five sixteenths to go, was in the mix for a small share in the stretch drive and was one paced late for a minor role. IPSUM GRATUS was bumped to begin, travelled like many after the start near the back of the field, was ridden for more between horses three furlongs out, shifted to the four path for the stretch run and had no finishing kick to give. JILLI MARIE travelled four deep in the pack of runners situated near the rear at the half, offered a mild run four wide outside horses to be in contention in the six path at the top of the lane and stalled in upper stretch. NORTHERN RUBY broke inwards to begin, trailed five wide outside horses down the backside, saved ground on the fence through the turn and passed a tired runner to the wire. HIT AND RUN was squeezed on the break, travelled in the two path near the rear at the half, was hard ridden midway on the turn making little gain and stopped in mid stretch.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: EPHRATA (GB) settled along the rail saving ground through the first turn off the pace, moved out two to three wide on the far turn, split runners three deep at the top of the stretch, bid outside in mid-stretch, dueled to the wire and kept on gamely to hold that rival at bay. INDY CHAMPAGNE settled outside a foe at at the rear early, moved to the rail and saved ground on the far turn, came out a couple paths in the stretch for room, bid between runners but couldn't get to the winner. STREGA set the pace racing in the clear and off the rail on the first turn, came out a bit at the top of the stretch, was challenged in mid-stretch and outfinished. ENSEMBLE (IRE) settled mid-division three to four wide, continued three deep into the far turn in behind runners, moved out five wide coming out of that bend, advanced between runners in upper stretch, ran on well late to secure the minor award. LADY MOONSHINE stalked the pace two to three wide, dropped back and faded in the stretch. GLORIANNIA raced forwardly two to three wide on the first turn moving out four deep for the run up the backstretch, was within range into the far turn floating five to six wide on that bend while dropping back some, failed to rally. SILVER MAGNATIZED tracked the pace from inside, switched outside a rival heading up the backstretch, went three wide into the far turn coming seven deep into upper stretch, lacked the needed late kick.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: WOODBINE RACE 11 1M Inner turf CR: 66. Maiden Claiming Purse 36300. INNER TURF FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $15,000, if for $14,000, allowed 1 lb.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BIG RANSOM took control from the outside to lead on the rail into the first turn, was left alone upfront down the backside, opened up on runners midway on the far turn, was headed outside in upper stretch and found more late to fight off the late closer in deep stretch. AIR FORCE RESERVE was hard held under the wire for the first time stalking five wide into the first turn, was steadied briefly entering the back straight to be near the back of the field, rallied four wide quickly circling runners three furlongs from home home to bid in upper stretch and could not get by on the outside late for the win. YORKVILLE travelled on the fence in the middle of the pack, advanced smartly on the rail through the far turn to be in range of the leaders straightening out for the drive, continued to fight inside down the stretch never giving up but had to settle for a non threatening third in the end. NGABE was fanned six wide on the initial turn, settled mid pack outside four deep at the half, rallied four wide around foes two furlongs from the finish and continued the late run a get up for a small share in the end. C R HOT SHOT settled near the rear down the backside, had nowhere to run behind horses at the three furlong marker, started to commence a run on the fence with five sixteenths remaining and finished with good late energy in the final eighth. PREETZAH'S STAR trailed in the early stages of the race, angled six wide seeing the field at the top of the lane and passed stragglers in mid stretch. PASSIONPLATE tracked the pacesetter on the rail, was content sitting behind the leader down the backside, was asked to go after the frontrunner three eighths from the prize, offered a mild run to be in the mix turning for home and faded between horses in the final sixteenth. SING DIXIE tracked two wide down the backstretch, was asked for more run midway on the final turn, offered little response and was not a factor in the run to the wire. TORY'S HOLIDAY was nudged on to keep position with runners on either side at the half, could not make any gains on rivals through the far turn and had no finish to offer in stretch run. SNOOKERED tracked four wide on the first turn, had a good position three wide outside alone in the third flight at the half mile marker, could not quicken with rivals on the far turn and gave way at the quarter pole.
